    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 14th with a clear focal point in **Yordan Alvarez**, who anchors the lineup with an elite 76.36 score. His matchup against Lorenzen is our most favorable offensive situation, bolstered by a 0.393 xwOBA and a prime #2 hole placement. While **Yordan Alvarez** serves as our power engine, **Caleb Durbin** (63.77) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (64.40) provide the necessary high-floor stability. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** remains a crucial engine for our scarcity-driven SB strategy, and despite a slight dip due to a high-efficiency catcher, his dynamic platoon edge against Nola makes him a locked-in start. Conversely, we are keeping a close watch on **Victor Scott II** (40.70); he sits right on the precipice of our roster floor, as his effectiveness is hampered by a bottom-of-the-order assignment and a difficult platoon matchup against Cantillo.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involves **Carson Benge**, who finished with a 39.80 efficiency score, narrowly missing the 40.00-point threshold required to displace our current starters. While **Carson Benge** benefits from a positive platoon split, the combination of a #9 batting order and a difficult encounter with Yamamoto makes him a suboptimal play for today's Roto caps. Management is also monitoring the 39% rain risk hanging over the contests involving **Chase Meidroth** (57.15) and **Junior Caminero** (62.77). While both are currently in the lineup, any delays could force us to pivot toward our bench if the game conditions deteriorate. We are also proceeding without **Christian Yelich**, **Zac Veen**, and **Colt Keith**, who remain sidelined via injury or roster displacement, leaving our depth currently thin as we navigate this mid-April schedule.",
